description:
The 1960s comic book adventures of The Phantom return in full, glorious color! Hermes Press will collect, beginning with this volume all 74 issues of The Phantom, starting with the Gold Key years. The Gold Key comic book version of the grand-daddy of costumed heroes, the Ghost Who Walks, is available again, digitally remastered to look better than the original books. The first volume collects eight stories in one volume.

This hardcover deluxe edition collects 1-8 comic issues from Gold Key's The Phantom 1962 series.
name: Volume One

volume.name: The Phantom The Complete Series: The Gold Key Years

description: What happens when the new weapons of mass destruction wield super-powers? That's the question posed in this gritty tale as a long-forgotten weapon from the Cold War resurfaces with destruction on its mind. This volume collects the disturbing finale to the engrossing series!
name: Book 2

description: Collecting issues #1-6 of the acclaimed maxiseries! In 1991, the Cold War ended without the two primary players ever facing each other in direct conflict. But now a long-forgotten Soviet weapon is awakened on one of America's many battlegrounds, threatening the global balance of power. Does America have an answer to...The Programme?
name: Book 1

description: The Li'l Depressed Boy has weathered many storms while on the road with Drew Blood, and returns home only to find Jazz waiting on his front stoop. How will LDB react to the return of the girl who broke his heart" Also: why is the lock on his door broken" Featuring a cover by the impossibly dreamy PHONOGRAM artist JAMIE MCKELVIE.
name: In A World Of Ghosts

description: Martha Washington -- prisoner, runaway, lunatic, soldier, and now seditionist -- has seen the future. It looks great on paper, but it doesn't work. The U.S. government is controlled by power-hungry nutcases. The ecology is a shambles. Everyone talks about the weather, but nobody does anything about it . . . nobody, that is, except PAX and the very expensive weather-control satellite, Harmony.
name: Martha Washington Goes to War

description: Covering the first two issues of Alejandro Jodorowsky's "The Incal", this volume tells the story of John DiFool a private investigator and occasional bodyguard who receives the Light Incal, a crystal of enormous powers, from a dying alien.
name: The Dark Incal & The Bright Incal

description: Covering the third and fourth issues of Alejandro Jodorowsky's series "The Incal", John Difool and his party flee through the City Shaft, a hidden world beneath the great pit city, while pursued by galactic President.
name: That Which Is Below & That Which Is Above

description: This volume, covering the final two issues in Alejandro Jodorowsky's, story brings to a conclusion the tale of the Incal.
name: The Fifth Essence Part One: The Dreaming Galaxy & The Fifth Essence Part Two: Planet DiFool

description: A collection of Jean Giraud's early work in black and white.
name: The Early Moebius & Other Humerous Stories

description: Venus, a global computer intelligence gone mad, is a heartbeat away from enslaving every mind on Earth. But Venus hasn't counted on her mortal enemy, Martha Washington, who captains a mission to observe the collision with a massive asteroid whose secrets may provide the key to Venus' destruction --- and the very key to Creation itself!
name: TPB

description: Learn how the Abramovici conjoined twins made their way from a small Siberian village to a traveling freak show, and finally to the depraved insanity of ARKHAM CITY. What role did Joker have in their journey to Arkham City...and also their horrific separation?
name: Separation Anxiety (Part 2)

description: After catastrophic changes in Zorro's world-events, Zorro begins to question everything he does and everything for which he stands.

Even with less than twenty minutes of "screen time" to his credit, the most popular character from the Star Wars trilogy is Boba Fett. Dark Horse offers a number of comics featuring the merciless bounty hunter, but it all starts here, in this trade paperback collecting Russ Manning's Star Wars newspaper strips. It was in these strips, which originally ran in 1979 and 1980, that Boba Fett made his very first appearance in print, making this a true must-have item for anyone looking to become a Jedi Master! The artwork has been colored, reformatted, and expertly retouched by Rick Hoberg, who worked with Manning on the original strips. Relive the adventures that thrilled readers seventeen years ago! Experience the very first comics appearance of the infamous Boba Fett (dated prior to his motion-picture debut)! And delight in Star Wars legend Al Williamson's new color cover, dedicated to Manning!
name: Classic Star Wars - The Early Adventures

volume.name: Classic Star Wars - The Early Adventures

description: An amazing collection featuring LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES #1-6 and the preview story from TEEN TITANS/LEGION SPECIAL #1! A bright, defiant, energized team of super-powered teenagers from different worlds forms a team of passionate activists crusading to leave their mark on a society that has forgotten how to fight for change!
name: Vol. 1

description: A new volume collecting LEGION OF SUPER-HEROES #7-13! As the team suffers infighting, the dream of a United Planets dissolves into hopelessness. Only a brawl between the Legion and the agents of Terror Firma can halt the coming invasion — but it's not without a great sacrifice!
name: Vol. 2

volume.name: Legion of Super-Heroes: Death of a Dream

description:
Bart makes an important archaeological discovery when he finds a frozen caveman in Lake Springfield. And after a mail-order mix-up, Homer's Christmas gifts to the family get delivered to different residences throughout Springfield - with surprising results! Then, Grampa Simpson explains the origins of eggnog, Christmas cards, and Santa's milk and cookies. Next, Bart tries to make some holiday cash by shoveling snow outside of Moe's Tavern. Finally, Homer has a billion dollar idea that will revolutionize wintertime play for kids. But will he be able to cash in?

  1. Guardian Snow Angel
  2. It's Snow Game
  3. Grampa's Christmas Origins: Christmas Cards
  4. The Iceman Cometh
  5. Grampa's Christmas Origins: Christmas Carols
  6. Billion Dollar Butt-ski
  7. Grampa's Christmas Origins: Christmas Cookies
  8. There's No Such Thing as Free Shipping
name: Guardian Snow Angel; It's Snow Game; Grampa's Christmas Origins; The Iceman Cometh; Billion Dollar Butt-ski; There's No Such Thing as Free Shipping
